## ðŸ’¥ The Real Issue: Itâ€™s Not Technical, Itâ€™s Cultural

The problem isnâ€™t just SCORM vs xAPI vs cmi5. The real problem is that **modern learning standards only shine when paired with modern learning practices**.

These standards were designed to support:
- Modular, reusable content
- Microlearning and just-in-time delivery
- Data-driven L&D decision making
- Blended, multi-platform learning experiences

But none of that works if youâ€™re still churning out 45-minute â€œcoursesâ€ packed into a single file.

### Bottom line:
> **SCORM is dying, xAPI is misunderstood, and cmi5 is underused â€” because weâ€™re still designing for 2004.**

Switching specs without changing process is like switching your pen and expecting your writing to improve.

